Your `tsconfig.json` is probably wrong. You&#39;re using both `files` and `include` to specify globs. `files` however is supposed to be used for [specific (relative or absolute) paths][1] whereas `include` can be used with globs.

If you merged the two paths into `include`, like this:

```
{
  &quot;compilerOptions&quot;: {
      &quot;outDir&quot;: &quot;./built&quot;,
      &quot;allowJs&quot;: true,
      &quot;target&quot;: &quot;es6&quot;,
      &quot;esModuleInterop&quot;: true,
      &quot;sourceMap&quot;: true,
  },
  &quot;include&quot;: [
      &quot;./src/**/*&quot;,
      &quot;./typings/*&quot;
  ]
}
```

your files should compile.

  [1]: https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/handbook/tsconfig-json.html#details

